# Frontend Panel Standards

## Interaction Design
- All destructive actions must show a confirmation dialog.
- Buttons that trigger long-running actions should show progress/disabled state.

## API Usage
- Call backend endpoints through consistent helper methods.
- Handle `status=false` branches explicitly and show readable error messages.

## Data Safety
- Do not render secrets directly in UI.
- Do not print sensitive payloads in browser console.

## Maintainability
- Keep functions small and split rendering from event binding logic.
- Use predictable IDs/class names for source/channel operations.
